sonville, Va.", "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "raw_lccn": "sn 85034357 ", "reel_numbers": ["0054286705a"], "resources": [{"files": 4, "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:vi:batch_vi_fortis_ver01:data:sn85034357:0054286705A:1930080801:0523/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn85034357/1930-08-08/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}], "rights": ["<p>The Library of Congress believes that the newspapers in Chronicling America are in the public domain or have no known copyright restrictions.  Newspapers published in the United States more than 95 years ago are in the public domain in their entirety. Any newspapers in Chronicling America that were published less than 95 years ago are also believed to be in the public domain, but may contain some copyrighted third party materials. Researchers using newspapers published less than 95 years ago should be alert for modern content (for example, registered and renewed for copyright and published with notice) that may be copyrighted.  Responsibility for making an independent legal assessment of an item and securing any necessary permissions ultimately rests with persons desiring to use the item.</p>\n<p>The NEH awardee responsible for producing each digital object is presented in the Chronicling America page display, below the page image  \u2013 e.g. Image produced by the Library of Congress. For more information on current NDNP awardees, see <a href=\"https://www.loc.gov/ndnp/listawardees.html\">https://www.loc.gov/ndnp/listawardees.html</a>.</p>\n<p>For more information on Library of Congress policies and disclaimers regarding rights and reproductions, see <a href=\"https://www.loc.gov/homepage/legal.html\">https://www.loc.gov/homepage/legal.html</a></p>"], "score": 14.504336, "shard": "02", "shelf_id": "sn85034357, 1930-08-08, Edition 1", "site": ["chroniclingamerica"], "source_group": "ndnp/vi", "source_modified": "2000-01-01T12:00:00Z", "subject": ["tazewell (va.)", "virginia", "tazewell", "jeffersonville", "newspapers", "united states"], "subject_headings": ["Tazewell (Va.)--Newspapers", "Virginia--Tazewell", "United States--Virginia--Tazewell--Tazewell", "United States--Virginia--Tazewell--Jeffersonville"], "subjects": [{"jeffersonville": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:jeffersonville&fo=json"}, {"newspapers": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:newspapers&fo=json"}, {"tazewell": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:tazewell&fo=json"}, {"tazewell (va.)": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:tazewell+%28va.%29&fo=json"}, {"united states": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:united+states&fo=json"}, {"virginia": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:virginia&fo=json"}], "timestamp": "2024-07-07T00:41:20.814Z", "title": "Clinch Valley news (Jeffersonville, Va.), August 8, 1930", "type": ["issue"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn85034357/1930-08-08/ed-1/"}, "locations": null, "method": "mets_filesec", "more_like_this": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/sn85034357/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/sn85034357"], "batch": ["vi_fortis_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "date": "18??", "description": ["Weekly Began in 1845. -v. 145, no. 36 (May 29, 2019). Called Jeffersonville until Feb. 29, 1892, then called Tazewell. \"Devoted to local and general news, agriculture and miscellany.\" Publisher varies. Numbering inconsistent. Microfilm available from the University of Virginia, and Bell & Howell. Archived issues are available in digital format as part of the Library of Congress Chronicling America online collection. By 1966, Southwest Virginia Newspapers, Inc. also published: the Richlands news-press; and the Saltville progress. Merged with the Richlands News Press to form the Clinch Valley News & Richlands Press. Description based on: \"Extra\" issued on June 28, 1867. Richlands news press (DLC)sn 00064818 Clinch Valley news & Richlands press (DLC) 2016270566"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-06-05T18:25:12.378Z", "group": ["newspaper-titles", "ndnp/newspapers", "catalog-split-04", "catalog", "united-states-newspaper-directory", "main-catalog-split-04"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn85034357/", "image_url": [], "index": 2, "language": ["english"], "latlong": [37.11484, -81.51955], "location": ["virginia", "tazewell", "jeffersonville", "united states"], "location_str": "", "lonlat": [-81.51955, 37.11484], "number": ["microfilm master", "microfilm service copy", "3792", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn85034357/1886-07-02/ed-1/", "sn85034357", "12696797", "univ of virginia", "sn00064375", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "1", "2024-04-11t06:56:48", "library of virginia, the", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn85034357/1963-12-26/ed-1/", "2024-07-06t20:47:42.603527", "new york hist soc, newsp proj", "online resource", "2016270566", "2158-2807", "sn00064818", "original"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "serial and government publications division", "clinch valley news (jeffersonville, va.) 18??-2019", "catalog", "chronicling america"], "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "score": 60.168068, "shelf_id": "Newspaper", "site": ["chroniclingamerica", "usnd", "catalog"], "subject": ["tazewell (va.)", "virginia", "tazewell", "jeffersonville", "https://id.oclc.org/worldcat/entity/e39pbjp669dy6cb3pwttdcmtrq", "newspapers", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-07-18T09:15:01.231Z", "title": "Clinch Valley news", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn85034357/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2021220121/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "18??", "dates": ["[1800 TO 9999]"], "description": ["Weekly Print began in 1845; Print ceased with v. 145, no. 36 (May 29, 2019). Called Jeffersonville until Feb. 29, 1892, then called Tazewell. \"Devoted to local and general news, agriculture and miscellany.\" Publisher varies. Numbering inconsistent. By 1966, Southwest Virginia Newspapers, Inc. also published: the Richlands news-press; and the Saltville progress. Merged with the Richlands News Press to form the Clinch Valley News & Richlands Press. July 7, 1886; title from caption (Chronicling America's website, viewed Feb. 10, 2021). December 22, 1922 (Chronicling America's website, viewed Feb. 10, 2021). Richlands news-press Clinch Valley news & Richlands press"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:23.371Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2021220121/", "image_url": [], "index": 3, "language": ["english"], "location": ["virginia", "tazewell", "jeffersonville", "united states"], "number": ["2021220121", "online resource", "862969120", "2767-1283", "2026-04-13t21:30:13"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "clinch valley news (jeffersonville, va.) 18??-current [online resource]", "serial and government publications division"], "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "score": 51.024334, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["tazewell (va.)", "virginia", "tazewell", "jeffersonville", "newspapers", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T21:01:49.831Z", "title": "Clinch Valley news", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2021220121/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2012203861/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1892", "dates": ["[1892 TO 1919]"], "description": ["Weekly(except Christmas) Began in 1892; ceased in 1919. Cf. Cappon, L.J. Va. Newspapers. Also issued in print. Mode of access: World Wide Web. Description based on print version record. Latest issue consulted: Vol. 21, no. 5 (Dec. 12, 1912) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed Sept. 4, 2012)."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:13.555Z", "group": ["n