"vi_fortis_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "composite_location": ["0/united states/", "1/united states/virginia/", "2/united states/virginia/tazewell/", "3/united states/virginia/tazewell/tazewell/", "3/united states/virginia/tazewell/jeffersonville/"], "contributor": ["library of virginia; richmond, va"], "date": "1930-08-08", "dates": ["1930-08-08"], "description": ["I Clinch Valley News ESTABLISHED 1845 Entered at the Tazewell Va post office as second class mail matter under act of Congress J A LESLIE SON Publisher TERMS OF SUBSCRIPTION In Advance By mail postpaid one year150 FRIDAY AUGUST 8 1930 MILK An estimate of the monthly re ceipts from the sale of milk in Taze well county an industry still in its swaddling clothes is from eighteen to twenty thousand dollars This is one of the bright spots and an industry that will eventually revolutionize the farming and cattle business of Taze well county The cattle business has always been a speculative one but the milk business although the returns under some conditions may not appear commensurate with the amount of la bor put forth can nearly always be depended upon to bring in a good re turn under all conditions A number of graziers of the county realize this situation and are governing them selves accordingly Few of the big estates can be adjusted to dairying altogether but the prediction is free ly made that many of the larger cat tle men of the county will in the very near future give some attention at least to the"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2024-07-07T00:18:02.642Z", "group": ["ndnp/vi", "library-of-virginia-richmond-va-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn85034357/1930-08-08/ed-1/?sp=2", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:vi:batch_vi_fortis_ver01:data:sn85034357:0054286705A:1930080801:0524/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=413&w=302", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:vi:batch_vi_fortis_ver01:data:sn85034357:0054286705A